      "note" : [ {
        "text" : "Physical contact is a sign of friendship between people of the same gender. Once you've built a trusted relationship, your counterpart might hug you, or even kiss you on the cheek as a greeting. If they hold your hand or arm, or lead you to another location hand-in-hand, don't pull away as you may send a message that you are not comfortable with them. "
